body:
Here is a simple interface definition:
```systemverilog
interface test_if #(parameter type sig_type = logic [3:0]);
    sig_type sig;
endinterface
```

The following module using the above interface fails:
```systemverilog
module test();
    test_if #(.sig_type(logic [7:0])) itf();
    localparam integer sigw = $bits(itf.sig);
    initial $display(sigw);
endmodule
```

However the following modules do *NOT* fail:
```systemverilog
module test();
    test_if #(.sig_type(logic [3:0])) itf(); // NOTE: this matches the default type in the interface definition
    localparam integer sigw = $bits(itf.sig);
    initial $display(sigw);
endmodule
```
```systemverilog
module test();
    test_if #(.sig_type(logic [7:0])) itf();
    initial $display($bits(itf.sig)); // NOTE: this uses the width directly
endmodule
```

The `verilator` command I am using is: `verilator -sv --cc test.sv`.

The `verilator` version I am using is: `Verilator 5.039 devel rev v5.038-237-g8868d459a` which was `master` as of today.

I am using Ubuntu 24.04 and compiled the `master` branch myself.

